Package: terraces
Type: Package
Title: Conservation of Empirical Statistics in Raster Disaggregation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Matthew", "Kling", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           email = "mattkling@berkeley.edu")
Description: Disaggregate raster data to finer resolutions such that all
    empirical statistics of the coarse raster (mean, variance, quantiles,
    full distribution) are preserved exactly through aggregation. Removes
    the regression-to-the-mean bias of standard bilinear and cubic
    interpolation by prefiltering the coarse raster with a precomputed
    inverse kernel.
